-- 
Radioactive Cesium Detected in Chiba Prefecture, Asahi says

-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 
2011-10-23T02:44:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/radioactive-cesium-detected-in-chiba-prefecture-asahi-says.html
A high level of radioactive cesium
was detected in soil of Kashiwa city, Chiba prefecture, near
 Tokyo , the Asahi newspaper reported, citing a statement by the
city yesterday.  Japan ’s science ministry will conduct further
tests on the soil and the surroundings today, the report said.
Some 276,000 becquerels of cesium per kilogram were found 30
centimeters below the ground’s surface, the Asahi said, citing
the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariko Yasu in Tokyo at 
 myasu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jason Clenfield at 
 jclenfield@bloomberg.net  